<p style="margin-top: 1em"><b>themer</b> - A script to
change theme of configs using a theme file. Inspired by
budlabs&rsquo; <b>mondo-generator</b> from the AUR.</p>

<p style="margin-left:8%; margin-top: 1em"><b>themer
[--dark|-D] <br>
[--auto-dark|-t</b> <i>&lt;am_time:pm_time&gt;</i><b>] <br>
--change|-c</b> <i>&lt;name&gt;</i> <b><br>
themer --new|-n</b> <i>&lt;name&gt;</i> <b><br>
themer --getvar|-v</b> <i>&lt;variable&gt;</i> <b><br>
themer --list|-l
themes|thememenu|vars|varmenu|default|current <br>
themer [--force|-f] --init|-i</b> <i>&lt;directory&gt;</i>
<b><br>
themer [--force|-f] --apply-single|-a</b>
<i>&lt;directory&gt;</i> <b><br>
themer --apply-all|-A <br>
themer --clean|-C</b> <i>&lt;directory&gt;</i> <b><br>
themer --updatelist|-u <br>
themer --help|-h <br>
themer</b></p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em"><b>dmenu</b> (my build),
<b>dmrap</b> - for gui menus <b>xsel</b> - copying variable
for <b>--list varmenu</b></p>


<p style="margin-top: 1em">[[/images/themer-gruvbox.png|gruvbox]]
[[/images/themer-i3.png|i3]]
[[/images/themer-nikes.png|nikes]]
[[/images/themer-redrock.png|redrock]]
[[/images/themer-solarized.png|solarized]]</p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em">Run with no options to create
defaults in <b>THEMER_DIR $THEMER_DIR</b> =
<b>$HOME/.config/themer</b></p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em"><b>--change|-c</b>
<i>&lt;theme&gt;</i> Change current theme to
<i>&lt;theme&gt;</i>. If <i>&lt;theme&gt;</i> is empty, a
rofi list of themes will be displayed.</p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em"><b>--apply-single|-a</b>
<i>&lt;directory&gt;</i> Apply current theme to
<i>&lt;directory&gt;</i>.</p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em"><b>--apply-all|-A</b> Apply
current theme to directories listed in
<b>$THEMER_DIR/.dirs</b>.</p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em"><b>--force|-f</b> Use with
<b>--apply-(single|all)</b> to force apply a theme, since
themes are not automatically generated from
&lsquo;template_&rsquo; files to speed up applying the
theme</p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em"><b>--dark|-D</b> Dark mode
(switches fgo and bg0).</p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em"><b>--auto-dark|-t</b>
<i>&lt;am_time&gt;</i><b>:</b><i>&lt;pm_time&gt;</i>
Dark/Light mode based on time of day. Uses 24-hr time
format</p>

